                            <comment id="14091661" author="tilman" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 05:36:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t get an NPE, I get this exception in both versions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Exception in thread &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;main&quot;&lt;/span&gt; java.io.IOException: Error expected floating point number actual=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;0.00000-79623834&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
	at org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSFloat.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(COSFloat.java:60)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSNumber.get(COSNumber.java:109)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseDirObject(BaseParser.java:1354)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseCOSArray(BaseParser.java:1072)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseDirObject(BaseParser.java:1281)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseCOSDictionaryValue(BaseParser.java:236)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseCOSDictionary(BaseParser.java:362)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseDirObject(BaseParser.java:1270)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.PDFParser.parseObject(PDFParser.java:593)
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.PDFParser.parse(PDFParser.java:194)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cause is a bad PDF:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;/Coords
[
9.107905
0.000000000000069029926
0.000000000000069029926
0.00000-79623834
]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14091736" author="jenhuang87" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 11:50:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, that&apos;s right.  I loaded the PDF with force = true.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14091739" author="jenhuang87" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 12:16:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wait why was this closed?  The NPE gets thrown after the document is loaded.  Shouldn&apos;t it at least check for not null and skip (like the previous version does) instead of erroring out?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14091740" author="tilman" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 12:22:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I&apos;m reopening so that I and others can think about it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14091774" author="tilman" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 14:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The paint method of the shadings was redesigned in the trunk a few weeks ago.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you building from source? If yes, please try this change:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;open the file PDPattern.java, and below the line&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;PDShading shading = shadingPattern.getShading();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;insert something like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (shading == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
{
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// some error message here
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Color.white;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll test it at a later time / day, the command line applications don&apos;t have a &quot;force&quot; option.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14091792" author="jenhuang87" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2014 15:13:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Downloaded the latest source code and added the snippet.  It fixed the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14092965" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2014 16:44:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can also use &lt;tt&gt;new Color(0, 0, 0, 0);&lt;/tt&gt; to get transparency on non-white backgrounds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14094231" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 16:08:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1617516 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1617516&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1617516&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2266&quot; title=&quot;NPE when converting page to image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2266&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2266&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: return transparent paint if shadingPattern is null&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14094242" author="tilman" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 16:12:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed as suggested by John.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jenhuang87&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jenhuang87&quot;&gt;jenhuang87&lt;/a&gt; in the long run, you should use loadNonSeq() and only use load() as a fallback option, i.e. if there&apos;s an exception.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14094298" author="jenhuang87" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 16:46:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will do.  Thanks for the quick fix!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
